DELETE OPERATIONS 
Use delete operations to remove documents that match a query filter. The query filter determines which records are selected for deletion based on the criteria in the query filter document. You can perform delete operations in MongoDB with the following methods:      * DeleteOne(), which deletes the first document that matches the query filter  * DeleteMany(), which deletes all documents that match the query filter 
